The Norwin Council of PTAs is in need of a nominating committee (of at least two people) to nominate officers for the March 12, 2019 meeting. Officer positions open for the 2019-2020 school year are: Vice President, Recording Secretary and Corresponding Secretary. The current president, Gretchen Fischer, and treasurer, Phoebe Korhnak, will be continuing in their positions for a second year. Please contact Gretchen Fischer at glfktm71@comcast.net if you are interested in helping with the nominating committee.

Our main duties are raising money for scholarships for high school seniors with a Dr. Seuss T-shirt sale and planning and hosting the Founder‚Äôs Day Dinner to honor our Outstanding Educators. We are also always available to our local PTAs and PTSAs for guidance if needed.

REMINDER: Calling all Science Fair participants! Mark your calendars for our upcoming Science Knights at the Norwin Public Library. This event will be held on Wednesday January 9th and Tuesday January 15th from 6:00 pm to 7:30 pm.

What is Science Knights you might ask? These evenings are an opportunity for the students and their parents to speak with volunteers from the High School science club about Science Fair. Students can learn about the three different types of projects, go over the grading rubrics, talk about their interests/hobbies and how those might translate into possible science fair projects.

The children‚Äôs library will also pull books from their stacks for students to peruse. Please join us on one of these nights!

What is Science Knights you might ask? These evenings are an opportunity for the students and their parents to speak with volunteers from the High School science club about Science Fair. Students can learn about the three different types of projects, go over the grading rubrics, talk about their interests/hobbies and how those might translate into possible science fair projects.

The children‚Äôs library will also pull books from their stacks for students to peruse. Please join us on one of these nights!

The Norwin High School Student Council is proud to sponsor the 9th Annual ‚ÄúPink Out‚Äù t-shirt campaign. This year‚Äôs t-shirt sale will open on Wednesday, 9/26/18 and runs through Wednesday, 10/10/18. The official pink-out game is scheduled for the final football game of the regular season, Friday, Oct. 26th, when the Norwin Knights football team kicks off against the Seneca Valley Raiders at 7:00 PM. Norwin School District (Official Site)
March 9, 2018 at 1:39 PM ¬∑

Dear Greater Norwin Community,

On behalf of Superintendent Dr. William Kerr, please see the link to a letter regarding the recent bomb threats at Norwin High School.

http://bit.ly/NHS_Incidents_Resolved

In short, the individual responsible for the recent bomb threats at Norwin High School has been identified following the investigation led by the High School and District Administration. Charges to be filed against the student by the North Huntingdon Township Police Department include three counts of Terroristic Threats (felony), three counts of Reckless Endangerment (misdemeanor), and three counts of Disorderly Conduct (misdemeanor).
